Errors I want to fix:

Driver Camera:

There should be a camera option on the driver’s side to allow them to upload their picture and pictures of their car.

Delivery Workflow:

When a user makes a delivery request, it should appear on the admin dashboard.

The admin can then send a price quote to the customer.

If the customer accepts the price, the admin assigns a driver to the customer.

The admin should also be able to view the customer’s information to contact them for negotiation if needed.

Price Negotiation:

If the customer wants to negotiate, they can request a call.

The admin can then call the customer to negotiate the price.

After negotiations, the admin can input the new price and provide account details for payment.

Once the customer has paid, they can click a “Sent” button.

The admin can then confirm the transaction and assign a driver.

Driver Workflow:

If a driver is online, they can accept a delivery request and access the customer’s contact information.

The driver receives live directions on a map to reach the customer’s location.

Upon arrival, the driver can click “Arrived at Customer Location” and call the customer.

After loading the delivery, the driver drives to the drop-off location, takes a picture of the delivered item, and clicks “Delivery Completed.”

Notifications & Tracking:

The admin should receive the delivery confirmation picture.

The customer should be able to track the driver in real time during the delivery.

The admin should also be able to track all deliveries on a live map.

On the map page, the admin can see all drivers online at each location.

The admin can search a specific location to check for nearby drivers and assign the closest driver to a customer.